status.description:
The status of the load balancer. Indicates whether the load
balancer is operational.

admin_state_up.description:
The administrative state of the load balancer, which is up (
``true`` ) or down ( ``false`` ).

tenant_id.description:
The ID of the tenant who owns the VIP. Only administrative users
can specify a tenant ID other than their own.

vip_address.description: The IP address of the VIP.

vip_subnet_id.description: The ID of the subnet on which to allocate the VIP address.

id.description: The unique ID for the load balancer.
